<p>I never said the jokes were not there, I just had absolutely no idea what they were supposed to do. I suppose I'm a bit at fault for phrasing it poorly &#8212; I essentially said &quot;Where are the jokes in this article?&quot;, when what I meant was &quot;What is supposed to make this article funny?&quot;. Having the list of jokes laid out for me is nice, but a collection of jokes all put on one page in one format does not an SCP-J make.</p>
<p>The problem here is that the main idea of the article is too obtuse to be funny. The recovery log, upon review, has potential. If the point here is to mock your 2000 contest entry, it's too narrow to work as a joke entry for me. If you want to effectively poke fun at conventions of the format as the whole, you can't devote the containment procedures to Star Wars jokes and play the description straight and expect people to immediately view it as a cohesive piece and understand what you're getting at.</p>
